{
  "stem": "25651.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Horowitz is written with a hey vav with a dot, which I read Horowitz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in Yiddish, everybody says Horowitz, and-- but you see it in German written text, and it's written Haurowitz, H-A-U, which is the German reform pronunciation of the Hebrew vav with a dot on top.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there were, there were there are lots of memories.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The next really impressionable memory was when I could first go to Maccabi Hatzair camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was when I was six.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was pestering my parents, you know, that I should go to Maccabi camp in the summer.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because in the summer, we were-- the house was full of men all the time and us two children.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "All the others, they were like giants, these fellas-- my brothers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When my brothers got angry with each other, and they fought-- I mean it was like the Laocoon, you know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a-- [LAUGHS] the whole house shook.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my mother would come in with the carpet beater, and she would separate them with this carpet beater.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she would lay into them quite, quite, you know-- because they wouldn't desist, sometimes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were boxing and all kinds of things.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I mean it was all-- that, you know, that sort of fight arises all the time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But it was wondrous to me as a boy to see these men, sometimes, fighting.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And you take sides, you see.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You'd have favorite brothers and not-so-favorite brothers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my, my first memory was, for example, going skiing when I was five.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my brothers went skiing, so I followed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a little girl in the town called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were completely sort of German reform, not even religious.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They never came to synagogue.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
